2. In these Rules, unless the context otherwise requires -
"approved" means approved by the Licensing Authority;
"Licensing Authority" has the meaning assigned to it in rule 5 of these Rules;
"petroleum in bulk" means petroleum contained in a receptacle of a capacity exceeding five hundred gallons;
"premises" in connexion with the storage of petroleum includes an underground kerbside tank and the pumps and other works connected therewith;
"to store petroleum" means to keep it in any one place otherwise than is necessary in the31 ordinary course of transit.

